  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Rinse the rice under cold water until clear. Add to a pot with 450ml water and a pinch of salt. Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat to low, cover, and simmer for 15 mins. Turn off the heat and leave covered for 10 mins."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "While the rice cooks make your keftedes. Peel and finely grate the onion. Peel and mince the garlic clove. Tear the stale bread into a bowl, soak in water for a few mins, then squeeze out the excess moisture."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "In a large mixing bowl, combine the beef mince, grated onion, minced garlic, soaked bread, egg, finely chopped mint, dried oregano, salt, pepper and cumin. Add a splash of red wine or vinegar. Mix well with your hands until smooth. Chill in the fridge while you continue."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Finely chop the spring onions, mint and dill. Zest and juice the lemon. Add everything to the cooked rice, season with salt and stir well. Set aside and keep warm."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Make the Tzatziki. Grate the cucumber and squeeze out the excess liquid. Peel and mince the garlic. Finely chop the mint. In a bowl, combine the grated cucumber, yoghurt, garlic, mint, juice of the lemon and salt to taste. Stir and chill."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Now for your tomato salad. Chop the tomatoes into wedges or chunks. Pit and roughly chop the olives if needed. In a bowl, combine the tomatoes, olives and capers. Drizzle with olive oil, sprinkle with dried oregano and season with salt. Toss and leave to sit."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Take the meat mixture from the fridge and shape into small meatballs. Roll each one lightly in plain flour."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Heat a generous drizzle of olive oil in a large frying pan over medium heat. Fry the keftedes in batches for 8-10 mins, turning until golden brown and cooked through."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Serve up the herbed rice with the keftedes, a big spoonful of tzatziki, and the tomato salad on the side and tuck in."
    }
  ],
